    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrent text of `vim.diagnostic.GetOpts`:\n`• {lnum}?       (integer) Limit diagnostics to those spanning the specified line number.`\n\nCurrent text of `vim.diagnostic.Set`\n`• {lnum}        (`integer`) The starting line of the diagnostic (0-indexed)`\n\n`lnum` in GetOpts is 0-indexed, not 1-indexed, but does not explicitly state this.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nDiscovered this because `vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor` returns `(row 1-indexed, col 0-indexed)`, but I cannot do `vim.diagnostic.get(0, { lnum = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)[1] })` by itself and have to throw a `- 1` in there to get it to work.",
